name: 1080Princeton
desc: 1080princeton's mission is to serve the Princeton community by creating evocative video and photojournalism projects that highlight the variety of issues, groups, and events affecting the student body.

name: 3D Printing
desc: Princeton 3D Printing aims to educate the Princeton community about 3D printing and make the technology accessible to everyone.

name: ACM Group, Princeton
desc: Fosters community among COS majors and those interested in computer science, brings speakers from academia and industry, and prepares for ACM Programming Competitions.

name: Advertise This
desc: Advertise This is Princeton's first and only marketing and advertising club. Our mission is two-fold: first, to increase awareness of marketing as a possible career path for students, and second, to provide students with skills to thrive in any industry.

name: Advocates for Justice, Princeton
desc: Princeton Advocates for Justice is an intersectional coalition of student groups dedicated to the advocacy and protection of basic human rights and dignity.

name: African Collective of Entrepreneurs, Innovators, and Technologists (ACE IT)
desc: The African Collective of Entrepreneurs, Innovators, and Technologists is for African and African-American entrepreneurs, entrepreneurs interested in Africa, and anyone who wants a taste of the "start up" culture through our student-run business ventures.

name: African Students Association (PASA)
desc: A cultural organization open to anyone from, interested in, or excited about Africa. Seeks to raise awareness on Africa & Africa-related issues and explores/celebrates the diversity of African cultures in order to foster unity/friendship amongst members.

name: Aikido Club
desc: The Princeton University Aikido Club allows students to explore Japanese culture, philosophy, and martial arts through the practice of Kokikai Aikido and provides the opportunity earn ranks from Kokikai Aikido International.

name: Alexander Hamilton Society
desc: The Alexander Hamilton Society is dedicated to promoting debate on basic principles and contemporary issues in foreign, economic, and national security policy, in defense of individual liberty, limited government, rule of law, and democracy.

name: Alternative, The
desc: The Alternative is a student group that offers an alternative social scene to the drinking and hookup cultures on campus.

name: American Foreign Policy
desc: AFP Magazine publishes editorials on a host of international issues and how they impact, and are impacted by, foreign policy of the United States.  The magazine is entirely student run and operated.

name: American Institute of Chemical Engineers
desc: Princeton student chapter of the American Institute of Chemical Engineers; provides social events and career opportunities for Princeton's Chemical Engineers.

name: American Physician Scientists Association
desc: The Princeton Local Chapter of the American Physician Scientists Association seeks to bring greater awareness of physician scientist careers and the MD/PhD to undergraduates through speaker events and conferences.

name: American Sign Language Club, Princeton University
desc: The Princeton University American Sign Language Club (PUASL) is dedicated to promoting American Sign Language and awareness of the Deaf culture in the University community.

name: American Society of Civil Engineers
desc: The ASCE Princeton Chapter is open to all students interested in the civil engineering profession. ASCE has two primary goals: to encourage students to stay in the field of applied civil engineering, and to provide hands on learning opportunities.

name: Analytics Group, Princeton
desc: The Princeton Analytics Group is a student-run consultancy that partners with for and non-profit corporate clients in solving real-world business problems.

name: Anglers, Princeton
desc: We are an organization committed to the promotion of fishing, especially fly fishing, as a form of outdoor recreation.

name: Animal Welfare Society, Princeton
desc: We are dedicated to the promotion of animal rights. Our efforts seek to raise awareness and encourage discussion of issues such as protection of wildlife and their environment, vegetarian/vegan options, and welfare of farm, research, and domestic animals.

name: Anime-Manga Princeton
desc: Anime Manga Princeton is a group for fans of japanese animation and manga. We meet for weekly showings, as well as for monthly events such as field trips, karaoke, and cosplay and manga workshops.

name: Anscombe Society
desc: Named after Elizabeth Anscombe, we promote sexual integrity through advocacy, speaker events, and debates. Past events include a debate on same-sex marriage, anti-pornography posters and campaigns, and discussions about the harms of hook-up culture.

name: Arab Society Of Princeton
desc: Geared towards exploring Arab heritage and culture and to unite Arab and non-Arab students.

name: Arch and Arrow
desc: Arch and Arrow is a creative outlet for student work.We hold our weekly workshops and open mic events, as well as accept submissions for our online and print literature magazine.

name: Architecture Association, Princeton
desc: Architecture Association of Princeton is devoted to promote interest in architecture, help interested students learn about careers in architecture/design fields, and create a space for undergraduates to explore architecture outside of class.

name: Armenian Club
desc: The Princeton Armenian Society is a community through which all students can explore, learn about, and celebrate Armenian culture.

name: Art Collective, Princeton University
desc: Promotes visual arts on campus through events, workshops, study breaks, and volunteering

name: Ascension Capital Development
desc: Ascension Capital Development promotes investment education through hands-on experience of managing real funds. The primary investment strategy we employ is simple/non-time consuming, suitable for core investments, and market-beating.

name: Asian-American Students Association
desc: The Asian American Students Association is dedicated to increasing campus consciousness about the unique social, cultural, political, and historical experiences of Asians in America.

name: Association of Black Women, Princeton
desc: An organization that aims to celebrate, unify and educate the community of black women on the Princeton campus.

name: Athlete Ally
desc: Athlete Ally is a group of LGBTQA athletes and straight allies dedicated to creating respect and support for all athletes regardless of sexual orientation, gender identity, race, class, religion, etc., and combatting homophobia and transphobia in sports.

name: Augmented Reality/Virtual Reality Club
desc: The Augmented Reality/Virtual Reality (AR/VR) Club also known as Princeton Arts & Technology (ArTech) is a club for those passionate about AR, VR, and other technologies and their interaction with the humanities world.

name: Autonomous Vehicle Engineering, Princeton
desc: PAVE is Princeton's undergraduate-driven robotics research group. We focus on autonomous vehicle technology, and are developing an autonomous Ford Escape and an autonomous Ford Fusion, but also participate in side competitions and community outreach.

name: Ballet Folklorico de Princeton, Grupo
desc: A dance group that promotes the spreading of Mexican culture and heritage through folkloric dance.

name: Ballet, Princeton University
desc: Princeton's only student-run dance group dedicated to the art of contemporary and classical ballet.

name: Band, Princeton University
desc: Provides music and entertainment at PU sporting events & year round gatherings.

name: Bee Team, Princeton
desc: If you're interested in beekeeping, as a hobby or otherwise, BEE excited! No previous experience necessary.

name: Beginning Uniting and Fueling Fitness (BUFF)
desc: A health and fitness consultation group dedicated to improving the general well being of Princeton students.

name: Bengal Tigers, Princeton University
desc: PUBT fosters unity among Bengali students on campus through cultural festivities, food, and educational activities. We welcome everyone to experience the culture and hospitality of the Bengali people.

name: Bhangra, Princeton
desc: Princeton Bhangra is a competitive dance team that performs bhangra, a high-energy folk dance originating from the Punjab region of India and Pakistan.

name: Bioethics Forum, Student
desc: Forum for campus and national undergraduate discussion on the most compelling bioethical issues of our time.

name: Biological Sciences Society
desc: The Princeton University Biological Sciences Society (PUBSS) aims to promote and foster a sense of community among students pursuing degrees and careers in the biological sciences.

name: Biomedical Engineering Society, Princeton
desc: PBMES seeks to provide resources and guidance to all students interested in biomedical engineering.

name: Black Arts Company-Dance
desc: BAC not only embodies the hip-hop talent Princeton has to offer, but also showcases Princeton’s commitment to diversity in culture and dance, the reward of exploring one’s passion, and the sense of community we build as the “purple family.”

name: Black Arts Company-Drama
desc: The Black Arts Company|Drama (BAC|Drama) is a student-managed theatre troupe dedicated to celebrating and exploring the cultural experiences of people from the African Diaspora through performance.

name: Black Student Union
desc: Our mission is to foster and maintain a community that supports the educational, professional, and social experiences of Princeton’s Black students.

name: Blended
desc: Blended is a student association for all mixed race students on campus. Blended is concerned with identity development, fostering an inclusive uniquely diverse community, and providing a forum for discussion about mixed race issues.

name: BodyHype
desc: Founded in 1991, BodyHype Dance Company exists today as one of Princeton University's most successful and captivating student-run dance groups.  A close-knit family in and outside of the studio, BodyHype is a group of versatile and engaging dancers.

name: Botany Club
desc: Through field trips, nature walks, partnerships with schools, and routine planting events, the Botany Club provides opportunities for Princeton students to learn about botany and engage with the local community.

name: Brass Ensemble
desc: Princeton Brass Ensemble is dedicated to showcasing brass musicians on campus. We perform all genres of music from pop to classical and jazz.

name: Brazil Society
desc: Club to promote awareness of Brazilian culture on campus and to host Brazil themed events.  Also, serves as a reference for students hoping to study abroad in Brazil.  Serves as a liason to the Princeton Club do Brazil (Alumni Association in Brazil).

name: Brewers, Princeton University
desc: The Princeton University Brewers are devoted promoting a love of beer, as well as providing its members with the opportunity to learn more about and brew their own craft beers.

name: Bridge Club
desc: We hold weekly contract bridge games and lessons on campus. We also travel to local and national tournaments and organize a competition team for the ACBL Collegiate Bridge Bowl every year.

name: British Society, Princeton University
desc: PUBS encourages pluralism and internationalism through celebration of British culture.

name: Brown Food Cooperative
desc: Brown Co-op accommodates up to 30 members each semester. Meals consist of a meat/veggie protein, veggies, starch, and a dessert. Each member cooks once per week with 3 other members. Members have access to the kitchen, ingredients, fun, and laughter 24/7!

name: Bulgarian Undergraduate Society
desc: The Bulgarian Undergraduate Society brings Bulgarian history, Bulgarian traditions, and the Bulgarian cuisine to the Princeton community, encouraging celebration and understanding of a culture residing in the eastern parts of the European continent.

name: Business Today
desc: Business Today's mission is to create a dynamic forum for influential business leaders to interact with top undergraduate students from campuses worldwide.

name: Business Volunteers, Princeton
desc: PBV is a pro-bono consulting group that takes pride in its dual mission of community service and business training. Our members are passionate about giving back to the community and making a measurable difference for our partner organizations.

name: Canadian Club, Princeton
desc: A social and cultural organization that is a home away from home for the Canadian students of Princeton.

name: Capoeira, Princeton
desc: Dedicated to spreading the Afro-Brazilian culture across campus.

name: Caribbean Connection, Princeton
desc: To provide all Princeton students and faculty a means for celebrating and learning about the many facets of life in the Caribbean Sea.

name: Cheese and Bad Movies Club
desc: We eat cheese and watch bad movies. Seriously.

name: Chess Club
desc: Weekly meetings to play casual games of chess. We send teams to tournaments every semester as well.

name: China Social Impact Project
desc: CSIP

name: Chinese Music Ensemble
desc: ChiME provides instruction and performance opportunities in traditional Chinese instruments and music.

name: Chinese Students Association
desc: Dedicated to celebrating Chinese culture through various festivals, charity, and social events throughout the year.

name: Chinese Theatre, Princeton
desc: A group dedicated to performing Chinese theatre plays in Chinese.

name: Classic Movie Appreciation Club
desc: The Classic Movie Appreciation Club functions as a resource for students to gain exposure to films throughout the cinematic era. With a special focus on black and white movies, the club provides access to films that students may not have exposure to.

name: Classics Club
desc: The purpose of this organization is to celebrate the cultures of ancient civilization through various events, such as reading groups, topic dinner discussions, and theatric performances.

name: Club de Lectura
desc: Dedicated to exploring Spanish and Latin American literature.

name: Coffee Club, Princeton
desc: Whole Latte Love is Princeton's coffee appreciation club, fostering an enjoyment and appreciation of coffee and its processes from farming to roasting to brewing. Join us and taste some awesome coffee!

name: Cognitive Science Society
desc: The Cognitive Science Society is a group dedicated to forming a community for interdisciplinary discussion about how the mind works. We welcome perspectives from all backgrounds, ranging from philosophy to engineering, linguistics, psychology, neuroscienc

name: College Democrats
desc: Political education, discussion & advocacy as related to the Democratic Party.

name: College Republicans
desc: Princeton College Republicans is the official representative for the Republican Party on Princeton's campus. We strive to promote conservative ideals and values among the student body, support Republican candidates, and host relevant speakers or events

name: Colosseum Club, The
desc: The Colosseum Club throws action-packed events on weekend nights. Colosseum Club: Seize the night! (Plus we are the masters of the annual dodgeball tournament)

name: Comics Club, Princeton
desc: The Princeton Comics Club provides a space to discuss comic books and related media (comics-based TV shows, movies, Comic-Con, etc.) and coordinates trips to comics-related events in the area.

name: Committee on Palestine, Princeton
desc: Founded in 2000, the Princeton Committee on Palestine (PCP) works to end the occupation in Palestine, defend Palestinian human rights, and raise awareness in the Princeton community about the Palestinian narrative.

name: Competitive Engineering, Princeton Unviersity
desc: Engineering and non-engineering students alike can compete together on year-long engineering/build competitions! In its pilot year, PCE participated in the SpaceX HyperLoop Pod Competition and has expanded to the NASA BIG Idea and RASCAL challenges.

name: Composers Collective, Undergraduate
desc: The Princeton Composers Collective is a collaborative group of undergraduates dedicated to the writing and performance of original student compositions. We workshop musical ideas weekly and hold several concert events each year.

name: Contrapunctus XIV
desc: tbd

name: Cooking Club
desc: Cooking club seeks to cook delicious food on Princeton's campus.

name: Corporate Finance, Princeton
desc: Educate. Inspire. Empower. We provide a platform for students to exchange ideas about corporate finance and learn from professionals in the industry. More importantly, we empower our members with a powerful network of support from fellow Tigers.

name: Cube Club, Princeton
desc: Promotes interest in solving and speedsolving twisty puzzles including the Rubik's Cube.

name: Data Science Club
desc: An organization to educate students in the field of data science, hosting data hack-a-thons, tech talks, workshops, and career opportunities.

name: Debate Panel
desc: Parliamentary debate team that competes in weekly tournaments, both domestically and internationally.

name: Decem
desc: Decem is a ten person classical sacred music consort.

name: Developing New Aspirations
desc: Developing New Aspirations (DNA) is a community of former athletes and artists who gather to discuss our pasts and prepare to find fulfillment in lives without our old activities.

name: Development Lab, Princeton
desc: We aim to promote and encourage engagement, literacy, and research with development and topics related to development through programming based on lectures by faculty both at Princeton and from other Universities.

name: Disability Awareness, Princeton
desc: PDA organizes awareness events on campus to promote disability awareness, education, and inclusion. Our main event is a Carnival for children with disability, their siblings, and Princeton students in November and April.

name: diSiac Dance Company
desc: diSiac Dance Company is one of the most popular dance groups on campus and pushes the frontiers of artistic expression through hip hop and contemporary dance. We put on two productions a year, in addition to workshops, company trips, and social events.

name: DoroBucci
desc: DoroBucci is Princeton's premier African dance group that aims to promote and encourage a deeper knowledge and appreciation for contemporary African dance and culture.

name: East West Theater, Princeton
desc: Princeton East West Theater is dedicated to promote inclusivity and creativity and encourage the exploration of Asian and Asian American identity through theater performance arts among the Princeton community.

name: Econometrics Society
desc: Supported by the Economics Department, the Econometrics Society consists of a competition team that trains for and attends the Econometrics Game at the University of Chicago and a conference-planning team hosts our own Game.

name: Effective Altruism Alpha
desc: Effective Alturism Alpha is a student group dedicated to promoting the intersection of Finance and Effective Altruism on campus. It is a hub for those interested in using their financial skills for positive social impact.

name: Eleusis
desc: Eleusis is committed to the informed, neutral, and interdisciplinary study of neuro-enhancement through academic discussion.

name: Ellipses
desc: Ellipses Slam Team is Princeton University's first spoken word organization. Ellipses members are dedicated to spreading the art and appreciation of poetry by sharing their stories and expressing their unique approach to writing and performance.

name: Energy Association
desc: Princeton University Energy Association brings together students interested in all aspects of the energy field, be it policy, technology, or business. Programs include weekly newsletters, employer site visits/info sessions, and high school engagement.

name: Engineering Council
desc: A student council serving our undergraduate engineering students. We organize events such as study breaks and the Excellence in Teaching Awards. We also help to orient freshmen and act as a liaison between the students and the SEAS administration.

name: Entrepreneurship Club
desc: The mission of the Princeton Entrepreneurship Club is to expose students to entrepreneurship, strengthen the entrepreneurial community at Princeton, and provide resources for entrepreneurial students to succeed.

name: Envision
desc: Envision enables future leaders to pioneer a brighter future through the prudent advancement of breakthrough technologies. We focus on addressing the benefits as well as the mitigation of risk.

name: Equality Project, Princeton
desc: PEP aims to realize full LGBTQA equality by fostering civic engagement and promoting social responsibility.

name: eSports, Princeton
desc: Princeton eSports is a casual/competitive club dedicated to playing online computer games such as League of Legends, Dota 2, Hearthstone, and Overwatch. Members hang out to play casually every week, and play competitively against other schools.

name: Expressions Dance Company
desc: eXpressions Dance Company, founded in 1979, is the oldest student run dance company at Princeton.  eXpressions specializes in contemporary dance, and also encourages innovative choreography across genres.  The company puts on two performances each year.

name: Farmers Market, Princeton University
desc: This group, operating in conjunction with the Office of Sustainability, works to organize a farmers market that will be held each spring on campus, bringing together vendors from all around the Princeton and the broader NJ community.

name: figments Magazine
desc: Figments is a speculative fiction magazine dedicated to promoting high-quality storytelling in the sci-fi, fantasy, and horror genres, to proving the literary and intellectual merit of these genres, and to forming a community for celebrating them.

name: Figure Drawing Club
desc: To be added

name: Film Productions, Princeton
desc: Princeton Film Productions is Princeton's only student-run film studio, producing short films that are written, acted, shot and edited by students every semester. Our mission is to allow students to share, create and collaboration on original art films

name: Film Society, Princeton
desc: Film screenings of independent and foreign films complemented by expert panels, informal discussions, and Q&As.;

name: Fintech, Princeton
desc: Princeton Fintech is a club designed to bring students together interested in fintech. We also aim to help students develop a passion for working on FinTech projects and connecting with innovators in the industry and academia.

name: Fire Hazards
desc: Princeton's only explicitly LGBT+ friendly a cappella group, originally founded in 1998 and rekindled in 2015. Pros: no-audition, no gendered voice parts, we sing our own arrangements. Cons: we're constantly on the run from Fire Safety.

name: Footnotes
desc: Fresh all-male a cappella since 1959 -- 300 Walker Hall Audition Room

name: French Society
desc: Supporting the development of a Francophone community within the University by providing a social and intellectual platform for French-speaking members of the Princeton community.

name: Fuzzy Dice
desc: Fuzzy Dice, Princeton's Most Attractive Improv Group, was founded in 2004 as the first troupe on campus to offer both long- and short-form improv. With a work hard, play hard mentality, we don't just perform great improv but also have fun doing it.

name: Gap Year Network
desc: We provide community and advocacy for all students who take time off. We focus especially on students returning from leaves in the fall and spring, so that they feel welcomed on campus and find any resources they need.

name: Garden Project
desc: We are a student-run, educational, organic garden located north of Forbes College at 79 Alexander Street. We hold workdays twice a week as needed and events throughout the year, including campfires, harvests, and yoga in our garden.

name: German Association, Princeton
desc: The German Association of Princeton provides German speakers and learners at Princeton University to interact with one another and develop a deeper understanding and appreciation of German language and culture.

name: Global China Connection
desc: GCC Princeton is dedicated to cultivating relations between China, the United States, and the international community.

name: Go Club, Princeton
desc: Play and promote the ancient board game known as Go, Wei Qi or Baduk. Provide lessons, host lectures, and more.

name: Golf Club, Princeton
desc: Promote the game of golf on campus through competition, instruction, and social events.

name: Gospel Ensemble
desc: We are a tight-knit, student-led choir that spreads the light of Jesus Christ to the Princeton campus and local community through music. Our repertoire includes a variety of traditional spirituals, hymns, and upbeat contemporary gospel music.

name: Greening Dining
desc: Greening Dining is a student group that meets monthly with Campus Dining to discuss and implement ways to make food-related practices on campus more sustainable.

name: Greg Test Group
desc: Greg's Test Group

name: Grind Arts Company
desc: Grind Arts Company creates boundary-pushing theatrical experiences.

name: Guild of Interdisciplinary Arts, Princeton
desc: An organization dedicated to fostering dialogue on campus amongst various disciplines and identities in the arts.

name: Gymnastics Club
desc: Princeton Gymnastics Club is a student run organization that gives students a chance to learn, practice, and compete at gymnastics. All are welcome, no experience necessary.

name: Hecate Society
desc: A student run grief support group on campus that meets weekly over dinner. If you have experienced the loss of a loved one, (i.e. parent, family member, guardian, friend) this is a place to grieve and share with peers who have similar experiences.

name: Hidden Minority Council
desc: Princeton Hidden Minority Council strives to advocate for first-generation low income (FLI) students, connect students to resources, and spur dialogue and greater discussion on Princeton's campus about socioeconomic differences.

name: High Steppers
desc: HighSteppers aims to expose Princeton to the the tradition of stepping, which originates from Africa and its Diaspora. We create music with only our bodies, using only stomps, claps, and shouts to energize crowds on campus and at off-campus competitions.

name: Historical Review, Princeton
desc: The Princeton Historical Review serves to provide Princeton students an opportunity to publish exceptional historical and area studies papers in a yearly magazine. Papers are selected through a competitive application process.

name: Hong Kong Students Association
desc: Aims to enrich campus life by bringing HK students & introducing HK culture to the University community.

name: Humans of Princeton
desc: An ongoing photo-documentary project brought by random encounters and the simple magic of asking questions.

name: In Bocca al Lupo Italian Theater Company
desc: In Bocca al Lupo is a theater group dedicated to bringing Italian theater, both in the original language and in translation, to campus through end-of-semester performances and improv Commedia Dell'Arte sketches throughout the year.

name: Innovation Princeton Journal of Science
desc: Organizataion is a general hub for all-things STEM on campus - we publish articles and put on events related to science communication and impact.

name: Institute for Chocolate Studies
desc: We make chocolate. We are Princeton's first student-run bean-to-bar chocolate factory.

name: IRC:  International Relations Council
desc: Center for Model United Nations at Princeton and forum for campus discussion on international relations and global issues. Hosts two Model United Nations conferences (high school, PMUNC, and collegiate, PDI) and competes at international conferences.

name: Irish Dance Company
desc: Princeton Irish Dance Company is a non-audition Irish dance team and Irish culture celebration group. We welcome dancers of all levels and have practices, events, masterclasses, performances, and study breaks throughout the year!

name: ISAP:  International Students Assoc. of Princeton
desc: Organzation that fosters bonding amongst international students, and exposes interested American students to cultures from around the world.

name: Ivy Council
desc: The Ivy Council brings Ivy League students together to facilitate the exchange of ideas. IVC seeks to develop student leadership through public service and global exchange opportunities. Additionally, students from all 8 schools convene twice per year.

name: J Street U Princeton
desc: J Street U Princeton works to engage Princeton students in a more meaningful conversation around the Israeli-Palestinian Conflict and to organize Princetonians to advocate for strong American leadership towards a two-state solution to the Conflict.

name: Japanese Students Association
desc: Brings students together to enhance Princetonians' understanding of Japanese culture.

name: Jewish Progressives
desc: The Alliance of Jewish Progressives is committed to a vision of social justice and equality and to the idea that all people deserve freedom and the opportunity to forge their own futures.

name: Journal of Bioethics, Princeton
desc: This publication is written and edited by undergraduate students from universities across the country. We work with a Technical Review Board of leaders in education, medicine, science, and ethics to provide a broad view of current issues in bioethics.

name: Journal of East Asian Studies
desc: PJEAS is an academic publication featuring student work on East Asian political, economic, and social affairs.

name: Juggling, Princeton
desc: Dedicated to the enjoyment and advancement of juggling and other physical arts.

name: Kalaa
desc: A dance company which performs various styles of Indian classical dance including Kuchipudi and Bharatnatyam.

name: Kardashian Lifestyle Klub
desc: A kommunity dedicated to living like the Kardashians through group events, konferences, and kontests. We accept all levels of Kardashian knowledge.

name: Katzenjammers
desc: The Ivy League's oldest co-ed a cappella group; we sing a wide variety of music from jazz and oldies to pop and classical.

name: Kindred Spirit
desc: KS is a Christian a cappella group spreading the gospel through song and to glorifying the Lord Jesus Christ. We offer inspirational outreach to Princeton and to our audiences everywhere through arch sings, community service, and local performances.

name: Koleinu
desc: Princeton's oldest and only Jewish A Cappella group, open to the entire Princeton community.

name: Korean Students Association of Princeton
desc: The Korean Students Association of Princeton is dedicated to promoting Korean language and culture through various events in the academic year.

name: Krav Maga Association, Princeton
desc: Group for all people interested in Krav Maga, the premier Israeli self defense form, of all levels, from complete beginners to advanced practitioners.

name: La Vie en Cello
desc: La Vie en Cello is Princeton University's only cello ensemble. The ensemble was formed in 2015 to bring fun and approachable music to Princeton University while maintaining the classical tradition.

name: Language Housing Association
desc: A group of students dedicated to connecting campus polyglots and language learners. All languages and all levels of fluency are welcome! We also advocate for the formation of a polyglot dorm on campus to house and facilitate language programing.

name: Language Project, Princeton University
desc: Our mission is to engage Princeton students in the global community by providing translation services to nonprofits that address the needs of diverse, multilingual populations, and by encouraging language-learning and sharing among Princeton students.

name: Latin American Student Organization (LASO)
desc: We are an organization dedicated to celebrating and recognizing the uniqueness of Latin American countries and cultures, by bringing together Latin American students and the general student body.

name: Latinos Y Amigos, Princeton
desc: Princeton Latinos y Amigos (PLA) is the pan-Latinx organization on campus. We strive to be an inclusive community through political, cultural, and social programming that showcases the diversity of Latinidad.

name: Latinx Perspectives Organization (PULPO), Princeton University
desc: Princeton University's Latinx Perspectives Organization is intent on diversifying what it means to be Latinx and raising awareness of Latinx issues.

name: Leadership for Change
desc: Leadership for Change envisions a Princeton culture in which leaders are not defined by position or title, but rather by students' motivation to develop themselves and others as leaders.

name: LEDA Scholars at Princeton
desc: LSAP strives to create a sense of community among LEDA scholars, to establish mentoring relationships between Scholars currently attending Princeton, and to reach out to LEDA Scholars who are considering attending Princeton.

name: Letterpress, Princeton University
desc: The Princeton University Letterpress is an organization dedicated to the study and practice of letterpress typography and book binding. We meet weekly in the Typography Studio in Lewis Arts Center to work on current projects and discuss future ideas.

name: Liars' Club, Princeton
desc: A community united by a love for games involving deceit. (Mafia, werewolf, resistance, liar's dice, etc.)

name: Libertarians, Princeton
desc: Provides presence, voice, and fellowship among those interested in the political philosophy of libertarianism.

name: Lobster Club
desc: No-audition improv comedy group.

name: Macedonian Association, Princeton University (PUMA)
desc: We're an organization that exists to celebrate Macedonian culture as well as attempt to bring Macedonian traditions, values and cuisine closer to the Princeton community.

name: Magic: The Gathering
desc: The Magic: The Gathering club provides opportunities for people new to the game to learn about, discuss, and play casually. We also provide opportunities for more experienced players to play competitively and provides information about local tournaments.

name: Magician's Club
desc: The Princeton Magician's Club is dedicated to helping its members learn, practice, and perform magic. We are open to anyone willing to learn, from the seasoned pro to the complete novice.

name: Makers Collective
desc: We are a group of tinkerers and inventors who love to build stuff. We operate Princeton's Makelab, an open resource for building projects on campus.

name: Malaysian and Singapore Student Association
desc: We organise activities for Singaporeans, Malaysians and anyone interested in the cultures, food and anything else about Singapore and Malaysia!

name: Mas Flow
desc: Más Flow is a diverse community of students devoted to celebrating Latin culture through dance. We hope that through workshops, performances, and socials, we can spread appreciation & love to the rest of Princeton about who we are and where we come from

name: MASJID (Muslim Advocates for Social Justice)
desc: MASJID - Muslim Advocates for Social Justice is a social justice group that provides space for Muslims and non-Muslims to come together around different social justice issues. MASJID gives a political platform for students interested in advocacy.

name: Materials Research Society, Princeton
desc: Princeton chapter of Materials Research Society. Fostering excitement in the understanding of materials in everyday life, as well as scientific research.

name: Mathematics Club
desc: Provides academic services to undergraduates with an interest in mathematics, organizes social events for math students, and facilitates the development of close connections between all members of the Princeton math community.

name: Midwestern Society, The
desc: A group to foster love for the American Midwest and its food, sports, and people. But mostly food.

name: Minority Association of Pre-Health Students
desc: We support pre-health undergraduates from minority backgrounds by building a community that guides students on a path geared towards health professions.

name: Mock Trial
desc: Princeton Mock Trial competes in American Mock Trial Association organized tournaments against other universities using fictional criminal or civil legal cases. Trials center around public speaking, acting, critical thinking, and improv skills.

name: Model Congress, Princeton
desc: The nation's premiere civics education program for high school students.

name: Motown Sound
desc: The Motown Sound is a musical group dedicated to the appreciation and performance of Motown music.  We are a diverse group of singers and instrumentalists who work together to share our love for this genre of music with the Princeton community.

name: Muay Thai Club
desc: The Princeton Muay Thai Club practices Thai kickboxing. Whether you want to train for self defense or want to get fit, we have a place for you. Absolutely no background needed.

name: Muse, Princeton
desc: Princeton Muse encourages open and honest dialogue through pairing strangers together for Conversation events.

name: Music Group, Princeton
desc: Princeton Classical Music Players hosts recitals and get-togethers for music lovers on campus. Classical Music Hour, an informal concert series, is held every Friday from 6:30-7:30 PM in Rocky Common Room. More formal events occur on a monthly basis.

name: Music in Mind
desc: Bridging the arts, sciences & humanities through music. Events include interdisciplinary dinner discussions, community service through music, social events/study breaks, and music-making.

name: Naacho
desc: Naacho is Princeton's premier South Asian Dance company. Naacho prides itself on presenting a wide variety of traditional and contemporary South Asian dances including Bollywood, Classical, Folk, Raas, Bhangra, and Fusion.

name: Nassau Literary Review
desc: A forum for creative artists and writers. Features the work of undergraduate students on a semiannual basis. Hosts literary and artistic events. Features personal and critical essays and reviews on its website.

name: Nassau Weekly
desc: Weekly news, humor and literary publication distributed free to all students on campus.

name: Nassoons
desc: The Nassoons are Princeton's oldest a capella group, founded in 1941.

name: National Society of Black Engineers
desc: Professional and academic development of Black engineers and students in the math/sciences.

name: Natives at Princeton
desc: Natives at Princeton is devoted to fostering dialogue and action on Native American and Indigenous issues here at Princeton.

name: Network of Enlightened Women (NeW)
desc: NeW is Princeton's premier group for right-of-center women. We aim to create a positive community of empowering women who discuss political issues and current events and ensure right-of-center female voices are an active part of the campus discourse.

name: Neuroscience Network, Princeton
desc: The goal of PNN is to promote a community of individuals interested in neuroscience both on and off the campus. The organization is divided into three committees (Events, Research/Mentoring, and Outreach) that plan their own initiatives and projects.

name: New Zealand Club
desc: PUNZS (Princeton University New Zealand Society) promotes inclusive and welcoming on-campus celebration of Kiwi culture.

name: Off the Record
desc: We are Princeton's Premier Hip-Hop and R&B; A Cappella Group. We sing exclusively these genres from multiple time periods and we are composed of singers, rappers, and beatboxers.

name: Old NasSoul
desc: Old NasSoul is an all-male a cappella group founded in 2006 dedicated to bringing R&B; and soul music to Princeton University.

name: Open Campus Coalition, Princeton
desc: Protecting diversity of thought and the right of all students to advance their academic and personal convictions in a manner free from intimidation.

name: Operations Research Society, Princeton
desc: The mission of the Princeton Operations Research Society (PORS) is to promote the field of operations research within the Princeton community and to support the development of students in the Operations Research and Financial Engineering (ORFE) department

name: OPUS 21
desc: Opus 21 is dedicated to bringing an eclectic repertory of chamber music to Princeton University and beyond. As cultural ambassadors, Opus 21 strives to broaden the public's interest in chamber music and collaborate with other peer institutions.

name: Orange Pan-Hellenic Association
desc: An organization celebrating Hellenic culture with the goal of fostering ties among the members of Princeton's Greek and Greek-American communities.

name: Order of Black Male Excellence, The
desc: An organization that provides a sense of fraternity and an arena for political, social and cultural discussions. OBME's mission is to promote and enhance the Black male experience on campus through a range of academic, social and service events.

name: Pehchaan
desc: Represents the Pakistani and Pakistani-American presence on campus.

name: Percussion Players Ensemble, Princeton
desc: The Princeton University Percussion Players Ensemble is a concert percussion ensemble open to all undergraduate and graduate students. We are dedicated to performing percussion pieces with a high level of excellence. We welcome all levels of experience.

name: Performing Arts Council
desc: PAC is the governing council for Princeton's student performing arts community. We work to promote an appreciation for the performing arts on campus by fostering artistic talent, while emphasizing diversity and inclusion of all forms.

name: Persian Society of Princeton
desc: Aims to introduce the Princeton Community to the rich Persian history and traditions.

name: Philosophical Society, Princeton
desc: Philosophical discussions, guest lectures and social gatherings.

name: Physics Students, Princeton Society of
desc: Sponsors academic and social events to foster open discussion, interaction, and a love of physics.

name: Pianists Ensemble, Princeton
desc: PPE is Princeton's multi-piano, multi-pianist family. We perform repertoire for up to five pianos, and we hope to build a supportive community of pianists who can collaborate together and put on exciting performances.

name: Ping Pong League
desc: The Princeton University Ping Pong League is a semester-based ping pong league-based tournament geared towards Princeton University graduates and undergraduates who are interested in playing casual ping pong matches.

name: Players, Princeton University
desc: A musical theatre organization that produces 4 to 6 musicals and revues a year. All shows are directed, acted, produced, and designed by students.

name: Poker Club, Princeton
desc: An organization dedicated to promoting poker as a tool to teach various academic skills such as game theory, risk analysis, and probability.

name: Polish Society
desc: The Princeton Polish Society is dedicated to promoting community among students of Polish descent and those interested in Polish culture, raising awareness about Polish language and customs, and providing a space to practice language and customs.

name: Pre-Dental Association
desc: Princeton Pre-dental Association aims to create a community of students aspiring for careers in the field of dental medicine that can be a source of support, advice, and education about the field and the process of applying to dental schools.

name: Pre-Law Society, Princeton University
desc: Provides the opportunity for students to evaluate careers in law and prepare for law school.rnrn

name: Pre-Veterinary Society, Princeton
desc: The Princeton Pre-Veterinary Society provides students interested in pursuing careers in the veterinary field with resources, support, and information regarding the veterinary school application process, possible career paths, and other opportunities.

name: Premedical Society, Princeton
desc: The Princeton Premedical Society is the premier student resource for undergraduates at Princeton University considering a career in healthcare. We are committed to actively providing opportunities, support, and mentorship to premedical students.

name: Pride Alliance
desc: A group of gay, lesbian, bisexual, transgender, queer, asexual, questioning and straight-ally students dedicated to promoting acceptance and understanding through organizing safe social spaces and events for the student body.

name: Princeton Acapellago
desc: Acapellago, founded in 2013, is one of Princeton University's no-audition co-ed a cappella groups.

name: Princeton Astronomy Club
desc: Princeton Astronomy Club works to create a welcoming environment to all those that share an interest in learning of what lies beyond the clouds and into the cosmos. Some activities include stargazing nights, discussions, astrophotography, and more!

name: Princeton Camerata
desc: Princeton Camerata is a chamber orchestra whose focus is performing Classical and early Romantic symphonic works with an emphasis on student involvement in musical and repertoire decisions.

name: Princeton Chamber Music Society
desc: Organization of chamber music rehearsal and performance opportunities for musicians of all levels, instruments, backgrounds, etc.

name: Princeton Ethiopian and Eritrean Students Association (PEESA)
desc: Dedicated to bringing some of Ethiopia and Eritrea to Princeton through various cultural, educational, as well as service-oriented events.

name: Princeton Filipino Community
desc: The Princeton Filipino Community is a cultural group dedicated to promoting and celebrating Filipino culture on campus and in the surrounding community through relevant discussions and activities.

name: Princeton for North Korean Human Rights (PNKHR)
desc: PNKHR aims to spread awareness of the human rights violations in North Korea and the difficulties that North Korean defectors face when resettling in South Korea. We also support North Korean human rights advocacy groups through fundraising efforts.

name: Princeton for Women in Politics
desc: Princeton for Women in Politics is a bipartisan student group dedicated to gender equality in politics, helping female political candidates + aspiring female student leaders. We encourage all students (of all genders) to become a part of our organization.

name: Princeton Law Review
desc: Princeton Law Review

name: Princeton MediHack
desc: Princeton MedHacks is a 36-hour medical hackathon during which students from interdisciplinary backgrounds team up to propose innovative solutions for challenges in healthcare.

name: Princeton Melee
desc: A group for anyone interested in watching, playing, or simply appreciating competitive Super Smash Bros. Melee for the Nintendo GameCube.

name: Princeton Progressive, The
desc: The Princeton Progressive (Prog) is the left-liberal political publication on campus. We publish three print issues per year and post articles regularly online (www.princetonprogressive.com).

name: Princeton Studios: Princeton University Film Festival
desc: PUFF is an immersive film festival targeting high school students around the nation. The one day event brings together creators, professionals, and academics to engage in screenings, panels, exhibits, and more.

name: Princeton Tonight
desc: Princeton Tonight is Princeton University's first broadcast television show, aiming to provide students with real-world television and film production experience through the Princeton University Broadcast Center and other campus outlets.

name: Princeton Traveler
desc: The Princeton Traveler is an online publication dedicated to inspiring the University's students to travel and discover the world outside the orange bubble.

name: Princeton Undergraduate Research Journal
desc: The Princeton Undergraduate Research Journal (PURJ) is a peer and faculty reviewed student publication highlighting research performed by Princeton undergraduates across all academic disciplines.

name: Princeton University Gun Safety
desc: Princeton University Gun Safety promotes the safe use of firearms, education about current issues and the history of firearms, and interest in shooting events, including athletic, competitive, and hunting.

name: Princeton Votes
desc: Princeton Votes aims to promote civic engagement and voter registration on campus.

name: Princeton Women in Economics & Policy
desc: Princeton Women in Economics and Policy is an organization for undergraduate women who are interested in studying or building careers in economics, politics, and public policy. Our mission is to leverage our collective experience and knowledge to facilita

name: Pro-Life, Princeton
desc: We seek to promote the dignity of every human life, in all its stages, from conception until natural death.

name: Public Health Review
desc: The Princeton Public Health Review (PPHR) is the only student-run journal on campus that provides a forum for all health-related discussions and showcases the outstanding global health research performed by Princeton undergraduates.

name: PUZZLES
desc: PUZZLES (Princeton University Zealously Zany Logical Enigma Solvers) is a group of students who love logic puzzles, word games, brain teasers, and secret codes. We host a school-wide Puzzle Hunt and work on bringing Escape Rooms to Princeton as well.

name: Quest Scholars Network, Princeton
desc: The Princeton chapter of the national Quest Scholars Network. Our main objectives are fostering a close-knit community of Quest Scholars on campus, and connecting high-achieving, low-income high school students to QuestBridge.

name: Quipfire! Improv Comedy
desc: Quipfire! is Princeton's oldest improv group, performing in over a dozen shows every year on campus and on tour in Los Angeles, Chicago, and New York City. Our alumni have gone on to write or perform with UCB, iO, Second City, and more.

name: Quiz Bowl
desc: Organizes and participates in academic trivia competitions. Practices always open to any who want to join in, and we will bring anybody that wants to attend to competitions so long as logistics and finances permit.

name: Racing Electric, Princeton
desc: Princeton Racing Electric designs, builds, and races high performance, sustainable electric single-seat race cars, and competes in the annual international Formula Hybrid competition at the New Hampshire Motor Speedway.

name: Radio Control Club, Princeton
desc: Learn to build and fly radio-controlled model aircraft. Design, Build, and Fly an aircraft for a mission to compete at AIAA's D-B-F.

name: Raqs: Princeton Belly Dance Company
desc: Princeton's only belly dance troupe is a welcoming and tight-knit community of women who love to learn and perform belly dancing. Members host workshops, give performances, and build a stronger belly dance community on Princeton's campus.

name: Real Estate, Princeton
desc: The Princeton University Real Estate Group aims to promote the real estate industry to current undergraduate students through its partnership with the “Princeton Alumni Real Estate Network”—consisting of approximately 1,000 active members.

name: Relay for Life at Princeton
desc: Relay for Life of Princeton organizes events to raise money for the American Cancer Society in order to fund cancer research, provide better support resources for cancer patients and survivors, and to raise general awareness about cancer.

name: ReModels
desc: With low rates of persistence in engineering for women, we seek to provide access to the field and to change the perception of engineering for future generations through an applied design experience and vibrant community.

name: Rise Up Princeton
desc: Rise Up Singing is a gathering of students who enjoy making music together. We meet weekly for at least two hours to play songs from the Rise Up songbook, and anyone is welcome to come.

name: Roaring 20
desc: A co-ed a cappella group from Gershwin to Gaga since 1983.

name: Robotics Club
desc: Club focused on small-to-medium size robotics projects, robotics classes, and outreach to high school robotics clubs.

name: Rock Ensemble, Princeton University
desc: We are Princeton University's only student-run, University-recognized rock band.

name: Rocketry Club
desc: We are an organization obsessed with everything aerospace-related. We launch rockets monthly, participate in competitions such as CanSat, IREC, and SpaceShot, and teach people of all experience levels about rockets!

name: Romanian Students & Scholars
desc: RSSA aims to promote the cultural and intellectual values of the Romanian People.

name: Russian Undergraduate Students Association
desc: An association of students of Russian language background or with an interest in Russian language and culture.

name: Scandinavian Club
desc: Cultural organization that aims to share our Scandinavian culture and tradition with the Princeton community.

name: Seniors and Youth (SAY)
desc: Seniors and Youth (SAY) is a program that breaks down communication barriers that exist between different generations and nationalities.  Princeton students and senior citizens in South Korea engage in weekly Skype calls to learn and empower each other.

name: Service in Style
desc: This student organization orchestrates and hosts an annual professional-quality fashion show to raise autism awareness and to fundraise for Eden Autism Services. This show, called Fashion Speaks, is the largest student-run charity event on campus.

name: Shakespeare Company, Princeton
desc: Student-run theatre company dedicated to performing and producing works of the Bard and his contemporaries, as well as modern works that respond to the original Shakespearean texts.

name: Shere Khan
desc: Shere Khan, named after the tiger in The Jungle Book, has been entertaining audiences with energetic, contemporary co-ed a cappella since 1993. Find out more at www.skprinceton.com!

name: Simulation Games Union
desc: A club for recreational board games and other non-computer simulation games.

name: Six14 Christian Dance Company

name: Small-Business Consulting, Princeton
desc: Princeton Small-Business Consulting is dedicated to serving local small-businesses while giving students the opportunity to gain practical consulting experience.

name: Smart Women Security

name: Social Sustainability

name: Society for Princeton Urbanists

name: Society of Hispanic Professional Engineers
desc: Works to promote the career development of Hispanic professional engineers so that they can serve as role models for the Hispanic community.

name: Society of Women Engineers
desc: Aids in the development of women engineers through events focused on mentorship, professional development, and community outreach for current and aspiring students.

name: Songline
desc: Songline Slam Poetry is a tight-knit spoken word poetry family dedicated to the art of storytelling. We perform spoken word and slam poetry through cohesive, themed shows, and compete in on- and off-campus competitions and slams.

name: Songwriters Society, Princeton
desc: A community of students at Princeton who create and perform their own original music. We host both informal gatherings to support students in collaborating on songs as well as formal performance events for students to show their songs.

name: South Asian Students Association
desc: SASA unites the culture of over a billion people from various South Asian nations through celebration, action, education and service. We strive to offer something for everyone to be engaged in South Asian culture!

name: South Asian Theatrics, Princeton (PSAT)
desc: The nation's first South Asian theatre company.

name: Southeast Asian Society

name: Southern Society, Princeton

name: Speak with Style
desc: Everyone benefits from effective communication. SwS is a resource for students to develop and practice interview skills, improv speaking, speechwriting, presentation, and idea-pitching through fun weekly practicums and workshops.

name: SpeakOut
desc: SpeakOut is a student run activist organization dedicated to raising awareness about sexual assualt and violence and helping to create a safer environment on our campus.

name: Spoon
desc: Spoon promotes culinary appreciation among students. We publish online articles and hold on-campus events to spread a love of food.

name: Sports Analytics, Princeton
desc: Conducts and publishes advanced analysis of sports statistics and the front office finances associated with each sport. We will give access to databases and resources in order to support innovative research, and publish findings online.

name: Stand-Up Princeton
desc: The only group dedicated to the fine art of stand up comedy. They perform in shows on campus and in the area.

name: Stripe Magazine
desc: Princeton's first online and on campus fashion magazine

name: Stripes, The
desc: The Stripes is a student-run publication focused on issues of race, culture, and minority identity.

name: Student Health Advisory Board
desc: SHAB is dedicated to promoting health and wellness on campus. We serve as liaisons between UHS and the student body and design and implement health-related projects to benefit our peers.

name: Students for Gender Equality, Princeton
desc: Princeton Students for Gender Equality (PSGE) is an activist group and an inclusive, intersectional forum for discussions of feminism, gender, sex, and sexuality.

name: Studies in Late Antiquity & the Middle Ages Journal, Princeton
desc: Princeton Studies in Late Antiquity and the Middle Ages is an interdisciplinary journal of Late Antique and Medieval Studies bringing together contributions from undergraduates, graduate students, and faculty members with interests in the period.

name: Sustainable Engineering and Development Scholars (SEADS)
desc: We are a sustainable education and outreach organization that is dedicated to providing a structured program for freshman and sophomore scholars to learn more about all facets of sustainability through discussions with professors and research projects.

name: Sustainable Software Initiative
desc: The Sustainable Software Initiative is a project-focused organization that aims to use software to address sustainability challenges on Princeton's campus and beyond.

name: Swara
desc: Princeton Swara is a student group dedicated to promoting Indian classical music on campus through student performances, guest lectures, and concerts featuring leading professional musicians

name: Swing Club

name: Sympoh
desc: Urban Arts: breakdancing, popping, hip hop-no auditions or experience required. Freestyle shows annually.

name: Taiwanese American Students Association
desc: Dedicated to promoting an understanding of and appreciation for Taiwanese culture and heritage on the Princeton campus.

name: TAMID
desc: TAMID Princeton works to develop the entrepreneurial and professional skills of undergraduate students through hands-on experience with Israeli technology, finance, and consulting companies. Find out more and apply at https://goo.gl/M98MNX .

name: Tangerine Magazine
desc: Tangerine Magazine is Princeton's food magazine, a seasonal publication dedicated to the fine art of eating. Our magazine is student written, edited, and published.

name: Tango Club, Princeton
desc: The Princeton Tango Club organizes Argentine Tango weekly workshops with guest instructors, social events, and a yearly tango festival.

name: TAPCATS

name: Tarana
desc: An avenue for individuals to appreciate, learn, create, and perform South Asian music.

name: Tau Beta Pi
desc: The engineering honor society. We recognize engineering students with a history of leadership and academic achievement.

name: Texans Club, Princeton
desc: The Texans club organizes social events for Princeton students regardless of their state heritage - though events do tend to have a Texan feel.

name: THAIGERS: Thai Students' Association
desc: We aim to promote an appreciation of Thai culture, deepen knowledge regarding Thailand, and assist Princetonians with the intention of traveling to Thailand. All our activities are for the benefit of all  members of the Princeton community.

name: The Daily Princetonian
desc: News, sports, and opinions from the Princeton University campus and community.

name: The Italian Society
desc: The Italian Society celebrates and disseminates Italian culture, history, and traditions within the Princeton community, with a particular emphasis on the culinary, cinematic, musical, and literary traditions of Italy.

name: The Playwright's Guild
desc: Theater group dedicated to the workshopping and performing of full-length original student plays. Our mission is to expand the opportunities for aspiring playwrights.

name: The Pool Club
desc: We are organization dedicated to furthering the presence of pool and billiards on campus.

name: Theatre Intime
desc: Produces approximately five plays and/or musicals annually. Hosts variety of other Princeton performing arts groups.

name: Tiger Capital Education
desc: Tiger Capital Education is dedicated to educating the Princeton campus on all things related to investing, connecting with buy-side professionals, and providing basic financial literacy.

name: Tiger Guard
desc: Tiger Guard is Princeton's one and only colorguard! We work to promote love of the arts on campus and foster school spirit. We spread awareness of colorguard as a sport and provide an outlet for those who wish to begin or continue their experience.

name: Tiger Investments
desc: Tiger Investments is a unique student organization of Princeton University that focuses on financial education and investment research. Our mission is to help members gain and apply the foundational tools they need to navigate the investing world.

name: Tiger Magazine
desc: Princeton's first, best, and only humor magazine since 1882.

name: Tigerlilies, The
desc: The Tigerlilies, Princeton's oldest all-female a cappella group, was founded in 1971 with the first class of women at the university.

name: Tigers for Israel
desc: Princeton's Israel advocacy and cultural group.

name: Tigertones, The Princeton
desc: Princeton's signature all-male a cappella singing group. Good friends and good music since 1946.

name: Tigressions, The
desc: Since 1981, the Tigressions have entertained audiences with their unique brand of bold, contemporary all-female a cappella.

name: To Write Love on Her Arms
desc: To Write Love On Her Arms (TWLOHA) is a non-profit movement dedicated to presenting hope and finding help for people struggling with depression, addiction, self-injury, and suicide.

name: Tora Taiko, Princeton
desc: We are a musical group dedicated to the practice and performance of taiko, or traditional Japanese drumming.

name: Tory, Princeton
desc: Campus journal of conservative and moderate thought. Published quarterly (in print and online) with an additional freshman issue.

name: Triangle Club
desc: The oldest touring collegiate musical comedy troupe in the nation! Student written and professionally directed.

name: Triple 8 Dance Company
desc: Triple 8 is Princeton's East Asian Dance Company. We perform styles ranging from lyrical, to hip hop, to traditional East Asian dance, to martial arts. No previous experience or Asian background necessary!

name: Turkish Students Association
desc: A society of Turkish undergraduate students which has as its goal promotion and awareness of the Turkish culture.

name: Umqombothi
desc: Umqombothi is Princeton's African a cappella group.  We bring vibrant music from several different African cultures of both a traditional and more contemporary nature.  We hope to spread awareness about the African continent.

name: Undergraduate Student Government (USG)
desc: The Undergraduate Student Government is the undergrad governing body, which envisions a dynamic community of Princetonians who are valued and supported in and outside of the classroom and empowered to advance the world we live in.

name: United World Colleges Club of Princeton
desc: The UWC Club at Princeton aims to reconnect UWC students and provide a social network which these students can access.

name: University Press Club
desc: Organization of student freelance journalists selected to write for professional newspapers and magazines.

name: Unix Users Group, Princeton
desc: Promotes and supports the use of free and alternative operating systems such as those built on Linux and BSD.

name: US-China Coalition, Princeton University
desc: To train undergraduate students to understand and analyze Chinese domestic and international policy from a Chinese perspective. To equip the next generation of leaders with the necessary tools needed to maintain a robust understanding of US-China policy.

name: Venture Capital Club, Princeton
desc: The Princeton Venture Capital Club is a student organization that looks to promote the creativity and confidence to succeed in the venture capital industry.

name: VERTE Magazine
desc: VERTE Magazine is Princeton's first publication dedicated to sustainable fashion, lifestyle, and design. VERTE aims to galvanize change in the campus community by featuring student writers, artists, and models.

name: Video Game Society
desc: Princeton's video game club. Organizes game- and development-related events and activities.

name: Vietnamese Students Association
desc: The Vietnamese Student Association seeks to expose the Princeton student body to traditional Vietnamese culture and customs through events such as film screenings and study breaks.

name: VTone
desc: VTone is Princeton's first East Asian Music Production Group. Our repertoire consists of a capella pieces as well as mashups, medleys, and remixes. We focus on East Asian music (Chinese, Korean, and Japanese), but we do English pieces as well!

name: Whig-Cliosophic Society, American
desc: The nation's oldest collegiate political, literary, and debating society.

name: Wildcats, The
desc: Founded in 1987, the Wildcats are a dynamic all-female a cappella group composed of confident, vibrant, and professional women who strive to redefine all-female a cappella, reflect the spirit of Princeton, and promote diversity and female empowerment.

name: Wilderness Society, Princeton

name: Woke Wednesdays

name: Women in Business, Princeton

name: Women in Computer Science, Princeton

name: Women in Science Colloquium
desc: We are dedicated to fostering discussions between female faculty and students in science, math, and engineering.  We welcome undergraduates, graduate students, postdocs and faculty to our events, which include dinner discussions once or twice a month.

name: Women Promoting Literacy
desc: Women Promoting Literacy (WPL) is dedicated to raising awareness regarding literacy issues in our local, regional, national, and international communities and engaging in local and broader initiatives to promote literacy, especially in local schools.

name: Women's Political Caucus
desc: The Princeton Univeristy Chapter of the Women's Political Caucus is a political organization that encourages political participation by women of all political parties who support an Equal Rights Amendment and the empowerment of women to leadership roles.

name: Wounded Tigers Network
desc: The Wounded Tigers Network (WTN) is a community of Princeton student-athletes that offer their support and guidance to injured athletes on campus.

name: WPRB

name: Wym'onStage
desc: Wym'on Stage is a group dedicated to sparking and promoting dialogue about gender equality on Princeton's campus through an annual performance of Eve Ensler's The Vagina Monologues.

name: Yoga Club

name: Young Democratic Socialists
